    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-09-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-09-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="673"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d673">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">760F.62/1358</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">British Embassy</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <p>His Majesty’s Government deeply appreciate the action taken by the President in
                    regard to the international crisis.</p>
                <p>The two messages enclosed herein,<note n="1" xml:id="d673fn1">Dated September 28,
                        1938; see <hi rend="italic">British Documents</hi>, 3d ser., vol. <hi
                            rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, docs. No. 1158 and No. 1159, p. 587.</note>
                    from the Prime Minister to Herr Hitler and to Signor Mussolini will show that
                    the action of His Majesty’s Government is much on the same lines.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-09-28">September 28,
                            1938</date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
